docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S1_T1.1_review.1.stdout.log:8:`internal/swim/contracts.go:107` declares `BaseSchedulePath`, schema requires it (`docs/specs/swim-review-schedule-schema-v1.json:7`), spec mandates "explicit only" sidecar location (`docs/specs/2026-05-14-swim-review-schedule-sidecar.md:18`), yet `ValidateReviewScheduleSidecar` (contracts.go:238) accepts the `base *Schedule` and never cross-checks the field. Sidecar pointing at a different base file is silently accepted. Either (a) compare `sidecar.BaseSchedulePath` to a base-path arg, or (b) add an explicit test-locked comment that path checking lives at the CLI loader (T1.2/T2.1). Today it is neither.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S2_T1.2_review.1.stdout.log:1:Review of T1.2 — "Add explicit review-schedule flag and env resolution contract" (claimed by phi).
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S2_T1.2_review.1.stdout.log:16:`_resolve_review_schedule_path` never stats the resolved path. T1.3 ("Verify fail-fast behavior for missing or invalid review-schedule paths") will likely flunk against this impl. Add a `must_exist=True` check that emits `{ok:false, error:"review schedule path not readable: <path>", subcommand:...}` exit 2 when `Path(resolved).is_file()` is false.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S2_T1.2_review.1.stdout.log:18:**C2. Schema file is untracked** — `docs/specs/swim-review-schedule-schema-v1.json`
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S2_T1.2_review.1.stdout.log:32:Every call site is `_ = _resolve_review_schedule_path(...)`. Acceptable for T1.2 scope (T3.2 is "thread review-schedule through swim execution"), but at minimum capture the result into a named local (`review_schedule_path`) and either pass it as `--review-schedule` to the Go subprocess or add a `# T3.2: thread this` placeholder. As written, a follow-up developer has to rewire four call sites and re-test.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S2_T1.2_review.1.stdout.log:35:Only the path-equality case is asserted. The "missing review schedule" branch (the more common operator failure) is unverified. Since the test suite for T1.2 lives here, add a case that unsets `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW`, omits `--review-schedule`, and asserts the deterministic error JSON + nonzero exit.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S2_T1.2_review.1.stdout.log:38:Works as a green-bar workaround, but the stub schema instance won't validate once schema enforcement turns on downstream. Either (a) point it at a fixture that satisfies the actual schema, or (b) keep T4.2's pre-T1.2 behavior unaffected by gating review-schedule only in commands that need it.
docs/impl/wp_sched_review/logs/S2_T1.2_review.1.stdout.log:46:**M3. `--ack-unknown` step bypasses review-schedule resolution** — `waveplan-cli:905-915`. Likely intentional (ack only touches the journal). Worth a one-line comment so the next reader doesn't "fix" it.
